  "texts": [
    "Unlike a Systematic Literature Review (SLR), a Grounded Theory Literature Review (GTLR) study does not aim to achieve completeness.",
    "Rather, it focuses on capturing the 'lay of the land' by identifying the key aspects of the topic and presenting rich explanations and nuanced insights.",
    "As such, while the process of a grounded theory literature review (GTLR) can be replicated, the results -the resulting descriptive findings -are not easily reproducible.",
    "Similarly, our study does not aim to be exhaustive, as it adheres to a grounded theory methodology.",
    "The chosen literature sample underwent thoughtful consideration, and although it is 123 not all-encompassing, we have taken steps to assess its representativeness."
  ],
